---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import LegalShell from "../components/LegalShell.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";

const lastUpdated = "April 26, 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy — Dome | Intelligent desktop for knowledge and research"
  description="How Dome handles data on your device, optional Google OAuth, cloud AI, and opt-in analytics — aligned with the open-source desktop app."
>
  <LegalShell title="Privacy Policy" eyebrow="— Privacy" lastUpdated={lastUpdated}>
    <div class="legal-highlight">
      <strong>Summary:</strong> Dome is a <strong>local-first</strong> desktop
      application. Your projects, files, and settings are stored on your device by
      default. The project does not operate a service that centralizes your full
      library. If you use <strong>optional</strong> features — cloud AI providers,
      <strong>Google Drive</strong> or
      <strong>Google Calendar</strong> via OAuth, or
      <strong>opt-in analytics</strong> — data may be processed as described below.
    </div>

    <h2>1. Data stored on your device</h2>
    <p>
      By default, content you create or import (notes, resources, attachments,
      settings, indexing data) is stored locally. The Dome project does
      <strong>not</strong> collect that content on its own servers.
    </p>
    <p>Typical local locations include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>macOS:</strong> ~/Library/Application Support/dome/
      </li>
      <li><strong>Windows:</strong> %APPDATA%/dome/</li>
      <li><strong>Linux:</strong> ~/.config/dome/</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Exact folder names may vary by install or platform; see in-app help or the
      repository docs if needed.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Google services (OAuth)</h2>
    <p>
      If you <strong>choose</strong> to connect Google, Dome uses
      <strong>OAuth 2.0</strong> (including PKCE for Drive) on your computer for
      optional features. You can disconnect in Settings at any time.
    </p>

    <h3>Google Drive</h3>
    <p>
      Lets you <strong>browse and import</strong> files you select into your
      local Dome library. Tokens are stored <strong>locally</strong> on your
      device — not on servers operated by the Dome project for sign-in.
    </p>

    <h3>Google Calendar</h3>
    <p>
      If you enable sync, Dome can read and manage events according to the
      permissions you grant. Tokens remain on your device unless another optional
      service you configure sends data elsewhere.
    </p>

    <p>
      Google’s use of data connected to your Google Account is governed by
      <a
        href="https://policies.google.com/privacy"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer">Google’s Privacy Policy</a
      >. This page does not replace Google’s terms.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Other optional third-party services</h2>
    <p>
      If you configure <strong>AI or cloud features</strong>, the app may send
      content (for example text from resources, chat messages, or analysis
      requests) to providers <strong>you</strong> enable, such as:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>OpenAI</strong> —
        <a href="https://openai.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >OpenAI privacy</a
        >
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Anthropic</strong> —
        <a
          href="https://www.anthropic.com/privacy"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">Anthropic privacy</a
        >
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Google (e.g. Gemini)</strong> when you add a Google API key or use
        Google as a provider —
        <a
          href="https://policies.google.com/privacy"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">Google’s Privacy Policy</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Local options (e.g. Ollama) follow the choices you set in
      <strong>Settings → AI</strong>. <strong>API keys</strong> you enter are
      stored on your device and are not sent to the Dome project’s servers for
      central storage.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Indexing and semantic search</h2>
    <p>
      Dome maintains a <strong>local semantic index</strong> (for example
      Nomic embeddings in SQLite) and <strong>hybrid search</strong> (vectors,
      full-text, and graph) over your resources. That data stays on your device.
      If you use cloud models for document or image understanding, that
      processing is subject to the provider you choose and your settings.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Optional product analytics</h2>
    <p>
      The app may offer <strong>opt-in</strong> product analytics (for example
      PostHog), controlled in the app and off unless you enable it, per the
      upstream project’s implementation.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Security</h2>
    <p>
      Protect your machine (password, disk encryption, OS updates). When you use
      OAuth or cloud APIs, also use strong account security on those providers.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
    <p>You can:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Access and export data through the application, where the feature exists</li>
      <li>Revoke Google or other integrations in Settings</li>
      <li>
        Remove local data by uninstalling the app and deleting its application
        data folder when appropriate
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>8. Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this page from time to time. The “Last updated” line above
      will change. Continued use of the site or app after changes means you
      accept the updated policy where applicable.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Privacy questions: <a href="mailto:alder.velasquezobando@gmail.com"
        >alder.velasquezobando@gmail.com</a
      >
      or
      <a
        href="https://github.com/maxprain12/dome"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer">open an issue on GitHub</a
      >.
    </p>
  </LegalShell>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
